This paper deals with data-driven models and their application in mechanical systems. It focuses on time series data and proposes a domain adaptation method that captures and transfers the dynamic and temporal causal mechanism of multivariate time series data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories, as well as the Systems and Control (cs.SY), Control Engineering (cs.CE), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) categories, which are all relevant to the study of mechanical systems and their control.
